So since Gemini was getting sunsetted, I explored having my own.&lt;p&gt;As I am a cheap rat, this weekend I built Themis, that works with my Codex/Claude subscriptions (I understood "claude -p" is ok again in subscriptions).&lt;p&gt;I wanted it open-source so it can help other indie devs or small teams, self-hostable (or local), drawing from subs and mostly, configurable so it works well with your own repos.&lt;p&gt;No big ambitions nor 1 billion startup here, just fun (so please don't roast ahah). If it is useful to even a few people, that's already great.&lt;p&gt;Happy to have feedback (especially on distributing the app!)&lt;p&gt;Ps: 1st HN contrib, hope it's the right format&lt;/p&gt;
